.SH "NAME"
telinit \- Chizzle SysV runlevel
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'\fBtelinit\ \fR\fB[OPTIONS...]\fR\fB\ \fR\fB{COMMAND}\fR\ 'u
\fBtelinit \fR\fB[OPTIONS...]\fR\fB \fR\fB{COMMAND}\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
\fBtelinit\fR
may be used ta chizzle tha SysV system runlevel\&. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. Since tha concept of SysV runlevels is obsolete tha runlevel requests is ghon be transparently translated tha fuck into systemd unit activation requests\&.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
Da followin options is understood:
.PP
\fB\-\-help\fR
.RS 4
Prints a gangbangin' finger-lickin' dirty-ass short help text n' exits\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-\-no\-wall\fR
.RS 4
Do not bust wall message before reboot/halt/power\-off\&.
.RE
.PP
Da followin commandz is understood:
.PP
\fB0\fR
.RS 4
Power\-off tha machine\&. This is translated tha fuck into a activation request for
poweroff\&.target
and is equivalent to
\fBsystemctl poweroff\fR\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB6\fR
.RS 4
Reboot tha machine\&. This is translated tha fuck into a activation request for
reboot\&.target
and is equivalent to
\fBsystemctl reboot\fR\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB2\fR, \fB3\fR, \fB4\fR, \fB5\fR
.RS 4
Change tha SysV runlevel\&. This is translated tha fuck into a activation request for
runlevel2\&.target,
runlevel3\&.target, \&.\&.\&. n' is equivalent to
\fBsystemctl isolate runlevel2\&.target\fR,
\fBsystemctl isolate runlevel3\&.target\fR, \&.\&.\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB1\fR, \fBs\fR, \fBS\fR
.RS 4
Change tha fuck into system rescue mode\&. This is translated tha fuck into a activation request for
rescue\&.target
and is equivalent to
\fBsystemctl rescue\fR\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBq\fR, \fBQ\fR
.RS 4
Reload daemon configuration\&. This is equivalent to
\fBsystemctl daemon\-reload\fR\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBu\fR, \fBU\fR
.RS 4
Serialize state, reexecute daemon n' deserialize state again\&. This is equivalent to
\fBsystemctl daemon\-reexec\fR\&.
.RE
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.PP
On success, 0 is returned, a non\-zero failure code otherwise\&.
.SH "NOTES"
.PP
This be a legacy command available fo' compatibilitizzle only\&. Well shiiiit, it should not be used no mo', as tha concept of runlevels is obsolete\&.
